texts.text: >The Liberators defeat Tiamat,
>and her giant body crumples.
That was too close for comfort.
No kiddin'. How's Nergal?
He's passed out over there but seems fine.
She, on the other hand, is too far gone...
*Sniffle*
Sorry, Tiamat. We really do feel for ya,
but we promised to protect our world.
Damn...you... Curse you all...
Am I really going to perish here...?
>Large tears spill from Tiamat's eyes.
Tiamat...
I cherished my husband and children...
Yet my children killed him...and betrayed that affection...
My love turned to wrath which ate me alive...
Why...?
I just wished...to treasure everyone...
>Tiamat's mouth slowly closes, and she breathes her last.
She truly was kind.
That's why she couldn't forgive those who betrayed her love.
*Chuckle*
...! You up, Nergal?
I couldn't deliver the final blow, but no matter...
Now Tiamat's corpse is mine.
The underworld will grow larger than ever!
You'd seriously do that?
Your lineage can be traced back to Tiamat as well.
Don't you feel any sympathy for your own ancestor?
None whatsoever. Only rage.
To carry the blood of such a repulsive creature infuriates me.
Bastard...!
I'll fight you too if you stand in my way.
We're all beaten to hell, but I, the God of War, will not lose.
Bring it on!
Let's drop it.
Calm down! I understand how you feel, but let's not be hasty.
It sucks, but I have to agree.
You choose to run? You have power, yet your hearts are weak.
Well then, I'll take this corpse. Farewell, Liber—
That's enough, Nergal.
What...? That voice...!
>They glance around for the speaker but find no one.
>The same voice calls down from the heavens.
Liberators, you have done us a great service.
I once conspired with several other gods to slay Tiamat.
?! This voice must be one of the killers she was after!
Hey, mind showin' yourself? Gotta put a face to a voice.
There is no need. My only role is to resolve the situation.
As minimal effort will suffice, I'll stay where I am.
I will now take Tiamat's body that lies there.
What?! Never! As if I'd let you!
Her corpse is rightfully mine!
Even YOU can't just take whatever you—
Silence, Nergal.
You, who failed to defeat Tiamat, dares to defy my will?
Ngh...
No, my lord...
Excellent. Compliance suits fledglings like yourself.
>Tiamat's body vanishes in a flash of light.
Ah! Her body...
It looks like that voice took it.
Well then, Liberators.
You've kindly subjugated Tiamat for us this time.
Therefore, I shall grant you this:
The title of "Hero."
"Hero"...?
Yes. Marduk was also a hero who slew Tiamat.
You should be proud to receive such an honor. You're heroes.
Never forget that reputation—
Cut the bullshit! No one asked you!
M-Megakin...?
"Heroes"? The hell? Don't twist our actions!
It was your arrogance that warped Tiamat in the first place!
And now y'all think you can do whatever with her lifeless body!
How long you gonna play around before you're satisfied?!
Bein' a hero is a huge deal.
But you're just tossin' the title at us outta convenience!
We don't need that shit!
If we're done here then get lost!
...What a foolish waste of my charity.
It is clear that you lowly humans cannot comprehend my will.
>The heavenly voice vanishes.
>Nergal suddenly disappears as well.
...They must have gone home.
Yeah.
Phew... Please don't scare me like that.
What if the voice had decided to attack?
I'd break that bridge when I got to it.
You guys were pissed too, right?
Yeah, thanks for telling 'em off.
I agree.
The voice alone told me that god is a pompous ass.
Tiamat fell for their charisma and paid the price.
We exist 'cause of our ancestors. Why treat 'em like crap?
Speakin' of which, I should stop by my family grave sometime.
...Yes, I think I'll visit my father as well.
I'll should help out with more than just the family finances.
Gee, I'm such a great daughter.
Exactly. That's the Japanese—no, human spirit.
Let's all treasure it.
In Tiamat's memory.
Calm down! I understand how you feel, but let's not be hasty.
